Class VCardDataType

  • java.lang.Object
    • ezvcard.VCardDataType

  • public class VCardDataType
extends Object
    Defines the data type of a property's value.

    • Field Detail

      • URL

        @SupportedVersions(value=V2_1)
public static final VCardDataType URL
        A uniform resource locator (for example, "http://www.example.com/image.jpg"). This data type is only used in 2.1 vCards. All other vCard versions use URI.

      • CONTENT_ID

        @SupportedVersions(value=V2_1)
public static final VCardDataType CONTENT_ID
        Refers to a MIME entity within an email.

      • BINARY

        @SupportedVersions(value=V3_0)
public static final VCardDataType BINARY
        A non-textual value, such as a picture or sound file.

      • URI

        @SupportedVersions(value={V3_0,V4_0})
public static final VCardDataType URI
        A uniform resource identifier (for example, "http://www.example.com/image.jpg"). 2.1 vCards use URL instead.

      • TEXT

        public static final VCardDataType TEXT
        A plain text value.

      • DATE

        @SupportedVersions(value={V3_0,V4_0})
public static final VCardDataType DATE
        A date that does not have a time component (for example, "2015-02-16").

      • TIME

        @SupportedVersions(value={V3_0,V4_0})
public static final VCardDataType TIME
        A time that does not have a date component (for example, "08:34:00").

      • DATE_TIME

        @SupportedVersions(value={V3_0,V4_0})
public static final VCardDataType DATE_TIME
        A date with a time component (for example, "2015-02-16 08:34:00").

      • DATE_AND_OR_TIME

        @SupportedVersions(value=V4_0)
public static final VCardDataType DATE_AND_OR_TIME
        Any sort of date/time combination. The value can be a date (e.g. "2015-02-16"), a time (e.g. "08:34:00"), or a date with a time component (e.g. "2015-02-16 08:34:00").

      • TIMESTAMP

        @SupportedVersions(value=V4_0)
public static final VCardDataType TIMESTAMP
        A specific moment in time. Timestamps should be in UTC time.

      • BOOLEAN

        @SupportedVersions(value=V4_0)
public static final VCardDataType BOOLEAN
        A boolean value ("true" or "false").

      • INTEGER

        @SupportedVersions(value=V4_0)
public static final VCardDataType INTEGER
        An integer value (for example, "42").

      • FLOAT

        @SupportedVersions(value=V4_0)
public static final VCardDataType FLOAT
        A floating-point value (for example, "3.14").

      • UTC_OFFSET

        @SupportedVersions(value=V4_0)
public static final VCardDataType UTC_OFFSET
        An offset from UTC time, in hours and minutes (for example, "-0500").

      • LANGUAGE_TAG

        @SupportedVersions(value=V4_0)
public static final VCardDataType LANGUAGE_TAG
        A standardized abbreviation for a language (for example, "en-us" for American English).

      • getName

        public String getName()

        Returns:

      • getSupportedVersions

        public VCardVersion[] getSupportedVersions()

        Gets the vCard versions that support this data type.

        The supported versions are defined by assigning a SupportedVersions annotation to the data type's static field (for example, CONTENT_ID). Dynamically-created data types (i.e. non-standard data types) are considered to be supported by all versions.

        Returns:
        the vCard versions that support this data type

      • isSupportedBy

        public boolean isSupportedBy(VCardVersion version)

        Determines if this data type is supported by the given vCard version.

        The supported versions are defined by assigning a SupportedVersions annotation to the data type's static field (for example, CONTENT_ID). Dynamically-created data types (i.e. non-standard data types) are considered to be supported by all versions.

        Parameters:
        version - the vCard version
        Returns:
        true if it is supported, false if not
